---
// About the Author. EDIT: bio text below and photo (public/author.jpg).
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import SectionHeader from "../components/SectionHeader.astro";
import CTAButton from "../components/CTAButton.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";
---

<Base title="About the Author" description={`About ${site.authorName}: 17+ years in completions, well intervention, stimulation and integrated well projects across 8 countries, MSc Data Science, practical industrial AI.`}>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-16">
    <SectionHeader kicker="the author" heading={site.authorName} />
    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[240px_1fr]">
      <img
        src="/author.jpg"
        alt={site.authorName}
        class="aspect-square w-full rounded-lg border border-line object-cover"
      />
      <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-4 text-slate-300">
        <p>
          I have spent <strong class="text-white">more than 17 years in completions, well intervention,
          stimulation and integrated well projects</strong>, working across field operations, engineering
          support and project management roles in Australia, India, Malaysia, the UAE, Bahrain, Angola,
          Chad and the UK.
        </p>
        <p>
          Throughout that time, Daily Drilling Reports were part of the daily operating rhythm: written
          under time pressure, reviewed for decisions, searched during planning, and revisited when lessons
          from previous wells mattered.
        </p>
        <p>
          After completing an <strong class="text-white">MSc in Data Science</strong>, I began combining
          operational well engineering experience with practical AI to build the tools I wished existed
          earlier in my career: systems that turn years of engineering reports into searchable knowledge,
          answer questions with evidence from the original reports, and run locally on confidential
          operational data.
        </p>
        <p>
          This book and its companion open-source project are the result. They are written for engineers
          with little or no programming experience who want to build practical, transparent and
          evidence-backed industrial AI systems from real engineering data.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <CTAButton href="/contact/">Get in touch</CTAButton>
      <CTAButton href={`https://github.com/${site.repoOwner}`} variant="ghost">GitHub profile</CTAButton>
      <CTAButton href={site.linkedin} variant="ghost">LinkedIn</CTAButton>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
